      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OSHLEY (7) raced parked when tackling a strong field at Bathurst last start so prepared to forgive that result. Came from the back row for second when fresh from a spell at Goulburn prior. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but she won the only time she raced here and should be approaching her peak. SILENT FEARS (6) led for a winning return at this circuit and distance two back then came from wider than this and did some work when third last start. Won the only other time she was third-up and is good enough to win a race of this calibre. THREETWONINE (9) has been racing at Menangle but scored at Penrith the last time she raced outside of the city so is better placed. LINE OF COURAGE (3) draws for a good showing.",
